<div id="review_1239459686" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1239459686" />
    <a title="Ben" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7640824-ben"><img alt="Ben" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1239459686?book_show_action=true">Mar 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ben" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ben" href="/user/show/7640824-ben">Ben</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19845522-revengeful-heart">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7640824-ben?shelf=literary-novels">literary-novels</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7640824-ben?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7640824-ben?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1239459686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15804120400094356898">Revengeful Heart<br/>Chrys Phillips (Author)<br/><br/>I am not really the right reader for a book that is about evil, and teenagers in a glossy town saving the world from promised doom. Give me the more believable Adrian Mole or Grange Hill for the realities of Teenage life. We have read this type of work before. Imagine, if you will Twilight, and another eight book epic about the growing pains of a boy wizard, and Chrys Phillips&apos;s work fits somewhere in there. That is not to say it is a bad, per se. There are</span>
  <span id="freeText15804120400094356898" style="display:none">Revengeful Heart<br />Chrys Phillips (Author)<br /><br />I am not really the right reader for a book that is about evil, and teenagers in a glossy town saving the world from promised doom. Give me the more believable Adrian Mole or Grange Hill for the realities of Teenage life. We have read this type of work before. Imagine, if you will Twilight, and another eight book epic about the growing pains of a boy wizard, and Chrys Phillips's work fits somewhere in there. That is not to say it is a bad, per se. There are some moments of pure adrenalin-filled action that move the story along, and the fact that it is Book One means that sequels will come in, that will take it somewhere else. I can see that this might well appeal to fans of fantasy, Science Fiction, or Magic Realism, as well as fans of Twilight or the diaries of Mr Potter. It just wasn't for me. There are good storylines and characters in here though, so there could well be a fruitful discussion for a book group in here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15804120400094356898" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


